OL,3,CAround 800,000 homes in Wales warned
OL,4,Cabout disused coal tips
OL,6,FUntil this body becomes operational,
OL,7,Fthe Welsh Government is currently in
OL,8,Fthe process of inspecting and
OL,9,Fcategorising all disused tips in Wales
OL,10,Faccording to their potential public
OL,11,Fsafety risks. They have now shared the
OL,12,Fexact location and categorisation of
OL,13,Fthese sites.
OL,15,FTips categorised as C and D tips have
OL,16,Fbeen deemed the highest risk and must
OL,17,Fbe inspected once and twice a year
OL,18,Frespectively. Categories A and B are
OL,19,Fsites which are "unlikely" or "very
OL,20,Funlikely" to cause public safety
OL,21,Fissues.
