OL,3,CAround 800,000 homes in Wales warned
OL,4,Cabout disused coal tips
OL,6,FIn February 2020, Storm Dennis also
OL,7,Fcaused a landslip at a disused coal
OL,8,Ftip in Tylorstown, Rhondda Cynon Taf.
OL,10,FFollowing this incident the Welsh and
OL,11,FUK Governments set up a joint Coal Tip
OL,12,FSafety Taskforce with the aim of
OL,13,Fregistering and assessing the
OL,14,Fimmediate status of disused coal tips
OL,15,Fin Wales.
OL,17,FLatest Welsh Government figures, as of
OL,18,FOctober 2025, have identified 2,590
OL,19,Fdisused coal tips in Wales, with the
OL,20,Fmajority in the South of the country.
